New Records: England won by 160 runs, the largest margin of victory in their ODI World Cup 2023 campaign
Key Match Events: Ben Stokes and Chris Woakes built a good partnership
Moeen Ali picked up his first wicket in the ODI World Cup 2023
Adil Rashid struck twice to dismiss Roelof van der Merwe and Aryan Dutt
Logan van Beek and Scott Edwards departed to Moeen Ali and Adil Rashid respectively
Pre-Game Insights: England have had a forgettable campaign, having won only one game in seven games they have played so far in the ongoing tournament
Netherlands have put up some memorable performances in this competition as they have won two and lost five games
Post-Match Reflections: Ben Stokes said: 'More pleased with the victory (than scoring a century), it has been a tough World Cup for us'
Jos Buttler said: 'Absolutely desperate for the win. Malan got us off to a flier. Partnership between Stokes and Woakes was fantastic'
Scott Edwards said: 'We didn't start well with the ball, let them get away from us. Bowlers did well to drag them back, but they got away again towards the end for a slightly above par total'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was contested at the Maharashtra Cricket Association Stadium in Pune
England need another win to book their place for the Champions Trophy 2025
Netherlands are not backing down! Eight runs off the over as Netherlands are 137/5 after 29 overs
